
// This Hyperlambda code snippet is used to construct an SQL query string by concatenating various parts. It retrieves an existing SQL string, appends an "order by" clause with specific fields for ordering, and adds a "limit" clause based on an argument. The [set-value] slot updates the [.sql] node with the concatenated string, while [strings.concat] combines the current SQL with additional ordering and limit criteria. The [get-value] slot fetches values from the existing SQL and arguments to be used in the concatenation process.
set-value:x:@.sql
   strings.concat:x:@.sql
      get-value:x:@.sql
      .:" order by keyword_count desc, keyword_density desc limit "
      get-value:x:@.arguments/*/limit
